news.title: Mumbai: BMC presents over Rs 74,000 crore budget for 2025-26
news.para: The additional municipal commissioners presented the budget to BMC Commissioner Bhushan Gagrani, who is the state-appointed administrator of the civic body, at the BMC headquarters here.

news.title: Elan Group to invest Rs 3,000 crore to develop residential project on Dwarka Expressway
news.para: Elan Group's project is a part of the company's over 50 acres township and will comprise of a total of 580 units spread across five towers, with a total saleable area of 28,70,000 sq ft.

news.title: Godrej Properties post net profit of Rs 158.20 crore in Q3 FY25
news.para: Godrej Properties' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,239.97 crore in Q3 FY25, a growth of 126.41 per cent from Rs 548.31 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Bhopal metro phase II will impact one-third less properties than phase I, claims report
news.para: Metro Phase II's 14.14 km blue line metro connecting Bhadbada Square to Ratnagiri is anticipated to commence construction before March's end, according to MPMRCL sources.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: Technopark to float tender for QUAD plan this month
news.para: Sources close to the project said that there are two QUAD projects—one will be built and operated by a co-developer and the second will be built and operated by Technopark.

news.title: Subhash Ghai, wife buy an apartment in Mumbai for Rs 24 crore
news.para: The property is located in 81 Aureate, a project by MJ Shah Group, spread across 4.48 acres and featuring 4 BHK apartments. It also includes three car parking spaces.

news.title: Zero property tax hike mooted by Pune and Pimpri Chinchwad civic bodies for FY26
news.para: While this proposal has already been approved by the municipal commissioner in the standing committee meeting of Pimpri Chinchwad Municipal Corporation (PCMC) last week, a similar proposal is yet to be approved by the Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC).

news.title: Goa government to form policy for setbacks for structures along highways
news.para: According to the guidelines of the ministry of road transport and highways (MoRTH), a setback of 40m is prescribed along highways, which is double the prevailing setback in Goa.

news.title: Realty firm employees booked for theft on another company's project site in Manesar
news.para: ​According to the complaint filed by Dhirendra Dadwal, director of Prominent Enterprises Private Limited (a real estate company), they had built a boundary wall around a land as part of their Swastik Green project in Manesar.

news.title: Allahabad HC dismisses plea against razing shops in residential society in Noida
news.para: The court upheld the Noida Authority's decision, stating that the occupants had no legal right to the properties due to the absence of an occupancy certificate and sub-lease deed.

news.title: Noida: Tribunal orders tenant to move out in a month, slaps Rs 20 lakh fine
news.para: Presiding over the tribunal, additional district magistrate (finance and revenue) Atul Kumar passed the order under UP Urban Premises Tenancy Regulation Act on Jan 21, warning of further legal action if the tenant fails to comply.

news.title: Luxury showrooms replace homes along Golf Course Road in Gurugram
news.para: Now, buildings on more than 60 residential plots in A, B and F blocks are operating as commercial establishments, housing high-end salons, gyms and vehicle showrooms, blatantly defying building regulations.

news.title: Haryana government formulates policy for e-auction of municipal land
news.para: According to the policy formed by the urban local bodies (ULB) department, auctions must be conducted through an online platform following prescribed procedures.

news.title: MahaRERA tells Pune collector to speed up recovery warrants against errant builders
news.para: The recovery warrants, issued under Section 40(1) of the Real Estate Act, authorise district collectors to attach properties and recover dues from defaulting developers.

news.title: BlackRock picks up 1.65 lakh sq ft office in Mumbai’s Goregaon to set up GCC
news.para: BlackRock Inc. has leased a total three floors in commercial complex Commerz III from listed developer Oberoi Realty at a rental of over 2.6 crore a month taking its total deal size to nearly Rs 400 crore including other charges.

news.title: WeWork India posts profit of Rs 174 crore in H1 FY25
news.para: ​WeWork India's total income stood at Rs 960.76 crore during the April-September period of the current 2024-25 financial year, according to the company's Draft Red Herring Prospectus (DRHP) filed with Sebi last week.

news.title: Asset monetisation plan of Mormugao port faces setbacks
news.para: ​Plans to lease out 50,000 sqm of prime land for warehousing and for a hotel in the port town, as well as a proposal to outsource the Deepvihar Primary School, the 100-bedded hospital, and the old administrative building for 30 years, failed.

news.title: NCLT approves Kingmaker Developers' amalgamation with Real Gem Buildtech
news.para: On November 6, 2023, DB Realty had executed a share purchase agreement to dispose off its 100% stake in equity and preference shares in Real Gem Buildtech for a consideration of approximately Rs 231.42 crore to Kingmaker Developers.

news.title: Macrotech Developers exploring to enter Delhi-NCR: Abhishek Lodha, MD
news.para: "We are exploring to enter Delhi-NCR housing market," he told PTI in an interview. Macrotech Developers is looking to acquire lands, either outright or joint development agreement with landowners, he added.

news.title: Anant Raj posts 54% increase in net profit to Rs 110.32 crore in Q3 FY25
news.para: Total income rose to Rs 543.97 crore in the third quarter of this fiscal year, from Rs 401.02 crore in the corresponding period of the preceding financial year, according to a regulatory filing.
